 This install applies to "Chuck Rock 2 - Son Of Chuck" floppy/cd³² © 1993 Core Design

 This install requires WHDLoad and DIC (floppy install only) to be in the path.
 Both can be found in the WHDLoad package.
 To install from a different drive than DF0: select installation mode Expert.

 The installed program requires 0.5 MB ChipMem and 1.0 MB OtherMem.
 It can be quit by pressing num '*' (key can be changed with Tooltype "QuitKey=").

 This installer requires the Chuck Rock 2 original CD³² or Chuck Rock 2 floppies (2).

 If you have problems with this installation please try and get a newer
 version of this package from the WHDLoad WWW-Page. If that doesn't help try
 some Tooltypes like NOCACHE, NOAUTOVEC, NOVBRMOVE, NOMMU, PAL or NTSC. If
 that also fails, please inform the author via the Bug-Report-Form which
 can be accessed on the WHDLoad WWW-Page or create a mantis issue directly
 at http://mantis.whdload.de

 For the full WHDLoad package, other installs and updates refer to:
	http://www.whdload.de/
 or	aminet:dev/misc/whdload#?
 and	aminet:game/patch/

 version 3.1 (05.03.2020):
 - Restored "up" control in menus when 2nd button jump is active (issue #004210)
 
 version 3.0 (09.03.2019) done by JOTD
 - CUSTOM2=1 enables blue/2nd button jump like in CD32 version
   (except that here a non-CD32 pad can be used)
 - CD32 play button pauses the game
 - CD32 bwd+fwd buttons quit the current game
 - CD32 fwd+yellow buttons skip levels (like HELP)
 
 version 2.4 (12.10.2006) done by JOTD
 - fixed a game bug revealed by the re-activation of the keyboard interrupt
   in slave version 2.2 (move.w #0,$68 instead of move.w #0,($68,A5))
 - potentially a game bug fixed because of the fix above.

 version 2.3 (06.10.2006) done by JOTD
 - ouch, the quitkey stuff was not very smart and crashed the game randomly
   (stupid game coding). Fixed
 - in-game keyboard was not working properly
 - quitkey also works on a 68000 / with NOVBRMOVE

 version 2.2 (08.06.2006)
 - enabled quit key in the intro section & menu

 version 2.1 (20.01.2005)
 - reworked install script (directory problem) 
 - slave revision bumped to 2.1

 version 2.0-B (02.09.2003)
 - fixed install scripts for both floppy & CD³² versions

 version 2.0 (10.08.2003) done by JOTD
 - Icons by Exoticons/Frank/Chris
 - Complete rework of slave/readme/install script
 - Fixed speed problem (was too fast on some machines)
 - Copylock protection removed
 - Keyboard routine fixed
 - HELP key skips level
 - CUSTOM1=1: infinite lives
 - Manual included
 - Nice icons by Frank
 - Source code included

 version 1.2

 - WHDLoad slave included (quits with QUITKEY)

 versions 1.x (JST only):

 - Runs fully from RAM/HD
 - Convenient installer script, lets you choose between install from CD or floppies
 - Patched memory routines so it runs with 32 bit fastmem
 - Uses JOTDStartup (JST)
 - Trainer mode : infinite lives
 - HELP skips levels
 - Quit key (F10 only during the game, LMB during menu)

Thanks to:
 - Walter Gierholz for providing the CD.
 - ANTHROX for their trainer code.
